Kaiba2,"Aug 3, 2025","English Version

In a world where unrest reigns over the oceans, pirates and the navy battle against each other, our Straw Hat crew is trying to find the legendary treasure, the One Piece, and thus our protagonist Monkey D. Luffy aims to become the Pirate King. One of the best anime there is and will ever be! With over 1000 episodes, this shouldn’t be too surprising. An endlessly vast world with just as many characters and an incredibly long and, above all, excellently written story. One Piece is peak anime, and there’s not much more to say. It’s simply incredible that this anime has been around
                  ...
for 25 years already and is still not finished. Over the years, you can witness an interesting transformation in anime. I recommend to anyone planning to watch the anime to start from episode 1. I’ve heard some people started with the New World to save time. (I can’t even put it into words, just don’t do it!). Also, you should be careful because spoilers can happen easily. And as a side note, the anime currently has over 14 movies!

German Version:

In einer Welt in der Unruhe über den Weltmeeren herrscht, Piraten und Marine gegeneinander Kämpfen, versucht unsere Strohhut-Bande den sagen umwobenen Schatz, das One Piece zu finden und so unser Protagonist Monkey D. Ruffy zum König der Piraten zu werden. Einer der besten Anime die es gibt und jemals geben wird! Mit über 1000 Folgen sollte das wohl nicht all zu überraschend sein. Eine endlos riesige Welt mit genau so endlos viele Charakter und einer unglaublich langen und vor allem hervorragend geschriebenen Story. One Piece ist Peak Anime und sonderlich viel mehr gibt es nicht zu sagen. Es ist einfach unglaublich das es diesen Anime seit bereits 25 Jahren gibt und bis jetzt nicht beendet ist. Über die Jahre ist eine interessante Veränderung von Anime mit an zu sehen. Ich empfehle jedem der Plant sich den Anime Anzuschauen das von Folge 1 an zu tun. Ich habe gehört das einige ab der neuen Welt angefangen haben um sich Zeit zu sparen. (Ich finde keine Worte dazu, mach es einfach nicht!). Außerdem solltet ihr aufpassen da es schnell mal passiert das ihr gespoilert werdet. Und als Rand Notiz, der Anime hat stand jetzt über 14 Filme!"
hamphield,"Oct 18, 2024","I started watching this anime when was showing in Cartoon Network back there and then I found out about the 4kids nonsense so I switched to Japanese anime, this is the first anime I watched in its original language and I was enjoying it, until I guess the Skypea season, I think this is where it went down hill or maybe it was since the beginning and I just figured it out, anyway...

I started to get frustrated by the pacing of the chapters, the same thing made me not like Dragon Ball, the feeler in the chapters that ruins the pacing I hate it, I
                  ...
that Toei stretch the emotion scenes so much. It makes it unbearable.

But what made me drop the anime was the fandom, I know you can be passionate about it (I'm a unapologetically fanboy of Naruto and I like Boruto FIGHT ME!!!!)  But I understand the critics this anime has and I still enjoy Kishimoto's work, but with One Piece, I just can't comprehend how unhinged they get when I complain about the pacing of the anime. They get mad.

Funny thing, those are the same reasons I don't like Dragon Ball either, interesting, another Toei anime... 

I don't hate Toei, they made Saint Seiya, Sailor Moon, Yu☆Gi☆Oh!, Digimon, etc. which makes me very frustrated 

Read the manga, let's see the reboot by Wit studio how will go, hope they fix this"
Ora_Poix,"Sep 4, 2025","One Piece is possibly the most polarizing show anime has ever created, up there with the Endless Eight and Domestic Girlfriend. For some, the best piece of fiction man has ever dared to write; for others, the worst thing since the Black Plague. I used to be a One Piece hater, but probably like most One Piece haters, I hadn't actually the show. Having watched a little bit of it, I can say that I'm still a One Piece hater.

First things first, the pacing is absolutely atrocious. If you have ever been recommended One Piece by a friend, it's likely that you've heard stuff like
                  ...
""It's not that bad"" or ""I promise it gets better later"". It is that bad. I started with One Pace, and immediatly, you can tell that it's slow. I then decided to commit a cardinal sin of entertainment consumption, and watched it at 1.5x. Even then, after spending 15 or 20 minutes watching an episode, you get the feeling that not much had actually happened. Like you could summarize the entire episode in one or two paragraphs. Even in 1.5x, you can see they spend far too much time repeating the same scene in different angles, or keep the same frame for 2 or 3 seconds too long, the humour is a very good reminder this is nearly 30 years old. It's excruciatingly boring, and there's not much you can do about it. 

Here's an example, just for you to get an idea. Upon getting into Arlong Park, I decided to commit what is probably another cardinal sin. Instead of watching the anime, I watched a movie called Episodes of Nami, an abridged version of the arc. Instead of the 4 hours it'd take me to watch it (at normal speed), the movie was roughly 2 hours long. And it was... good. I was entertained, I was interested in the story, I actually cared about the show! You felt that it had told everything that it was supossed to tell, and it took half the time of the normal series. 

Now, if this was the only problem, It would be fine. Not for me, definitely, but maybe it did get good later. From what I've seen in discussions, Arlong Park is a very highly rated arc, one of the best pre-timeskip and even overall. Was it good? No. For starters, you get a lot of reminders that this is, in fact, an action shonen. The carachters are all a bit stupid, and a lot of stuff doesn't make sense upon any sort of reflection, but I've learned to deal with that.Even discounting that, it's just plain. This arc, and every other before it, all more or less follow the same formula: The crew gets into the island -> They discover the conflict, the good guys and the bad guys -> They fight a little, and you get some flashbacks into important carachters -> The crew decides to intervene and save the day. 
There's not a lot of complexity, the enemies are cartoonishly bad, the good guys cartoonishly victims. Even the main carachters, at least until now, are extremely simple. You can sum up all of them as: Something traumatic happened in their childhood, so now they want X or do Y because of it. Luffy doesn't get any monologues, in fact I'm pretty sure nothing goes across that man's mind 80% of the time. Reminder, this is one of the most highly rated arcs. It felt a bit like Demon Slayer, but instead of watching the best animation the industry has to offer, you're watching a weekly show from 1997. I have a snarky little suspicion that this formula doesn't change much, and I'd rather eat a 7mm round instead of continuing my suffering to check it out. 

As for the most praised thing in this show, the worldbuilding, there was barely any of it. Some carachters showed up, some groups namedropped. but it was all pretty barebones. The worldbuilding probably suffers the same pacing problem as the rest of the show, and even the most basic facts about the world of One Piece are told in bits and pieces across a hundred episodes. 

Overall, 5/10, a kind 5/10 at that. Unless you have a lot of time and a looooooooooooooooooot of patience on your hands, this show is not for you."
SPACE_KOBRA,"Aug 26, 2008","man, what can i say about this show....in america i 1st saw one piece on fox for kids, and i thought it was the worst shit i had ever seen in my life, because us sloppy americans like to make &quot;cartoons&quot; kid friendly so they took all the great things japan did with one piece out and made it really gay, not to mention the voice acting was TERRIBLE.....BUT I checked it out again in 2007 and found it bareable..........as the show moved on i just thought wow i love this show......luffy and the rest of the characters are great......i even like the characters that
                  ...
i wouldnt necissarily like if they were on another show ( ussop and nami) this epic is great, they do everything really well. when theres drama its great..when there comedy and funny as hell, the fighting is great, the Story is fantastic,i love everything about one piece. hence the reason why its my favorite show, idk when a show is going to knock it out of the number one spot, but when it comes along, ill be shocked."
DeathHormone,"May 14, 2009","*Spoiler Free Review*
One Piece is an Anime about Pirates, Mainly one crew of Pirates called ""Straw Hats"". It is a action adventure anime, where the characters have special powers and are super strong.

The Main storyline isn't that amazing, It's typical boy has a dream, boy goes out to obtain said dream, but what is amazing is the side storys that mixes into the main story, and there are tons, most of these are character background or goals, but it all fits in very nice, due to how big the One Piece world is, and how well the characters are devolped. The main reason I gave
                  ...
Story a 7 is due to the real main story, it's been done tons of times.

The artwork and animation in this Anime gets alot of negitave response, but on the whole i'd say its average, its not rubbish by any standard, and sometimes has some very nice effects, But it's not the best out there. Don't be put off by the people who list the animation as why one piece sucks, because its the most stupidest thing ever, people still play old video games and watch old anime, do people complain about the graphics/ animation in them? No. 

The Sound is this Anime is epic, The Voice actors are very good at their jobs eppeically Zoro and Luffy. The Music is full of epic win! Most of all, all of the sound effects sound like the real thing, which is always a good thing, you know somethings up when a sword sounds like a wet fish hiting a rock.

The Characters are very well devolped, even the majority of the lesser know characters have somewhat of a devolped background and continue to devolpe in the anime, something most animes don't have. I like that One piece does this, as it adds to the well written universe the creators have made, and it also allows the One Piece world to expand.

To finish things off, the amount of enjoyment i get out of this anime has only ever been rivaled by Death Note, comparing it to other animes of the same genre however, nothing has came close to topping how well everything in One piece goes, and sometimes I hope that the show will never end, because I find it that much of an enjoyment to watch.

So go check it out, if it sounds intresting to you, if not, well i guess my review skills suck, and you should go read a diffrent one piece review :P"
Patrorex,"Jan 16, 2025","I used to like One Piece a lot until the Whole Cake Island Arc, but from that point on, the anime seemed too childish. I think my opinion changed after watching other anime where the main character has a decent level of intelligence and delivers a final blow to defeat the enemy instead of chit-chatting. In One Piece, they often waste time talking, allowing enemies to return and cause more trouble later.

That said, if you are new to anime, you will most likely love it, just like I did. However, if you’ve watched many other series where the protagonist acts decisively and doesn’t hesitate to
                  ...
finish off an enemy, you might find One Piece frustrating.

I’ll probably watch a story recap after one or two years when the series is complete."
andrex316,"Jan 6, 2009","It's just sooo sad to see how shows like Bleach and Naruto are more popular than One Piece...it just goes to show how understimated this show rlly is...

This is one of the few anime that have evrtyhing you would want in any series, from awsome action sequence, to hilarious comedy and then to drama. This is the only series, besides elfen lied, that has made real tears come from me.

People shouldn't put a barrier between this show because the art style, which is what most ppl have problems with in this series, just because the style is unique and trying something new is not bad
                  ...
at all. Also, it shouldnt be judged by the bad job done on the dubbing of the series which totally killed it.

There is a character for evryone here and anyone that truly calls themselves an anime fan should definitely give this show a try. It's no mistake the manga is #1 in Japan and since the naime is exactly like the manga...well u kno.

Anyway, just don't judge a book by its cover and give it a shot!!!"
Shineix,"May 18, 2025","If you told me from a year ago I would watch One Piece, I would genuinely laugh but here I am fully caught up on the anime and manga and being one of the biggest fans. 

I can't put into words how much my love for one piece is, it was a journey for me, a long one but one I don't regret at all. Coming home and watching it, seeing the characters go through arcs and difficulties was just amazing and I felt so invested in it.

Some of my favourite things about this anime are of course the cast of characters, main ones and
                  ...
side, each being so perfect that there's not a single arc's characters I disliked, the world is so detailed and planned out perfectly, the antagonists which are all so good in their own unique ways, the story arcs and how each are actually significant and don't get thrown away as the plot progresses, the entertainment and comedy, the fights and emotions, I could go on for hours.

I can understand why people get turned off from the length, I do agree that the pacing is bad but mindlessly hating or watching it not to enjoy but to force yourself will never make you like One Piece. I'd say start it if you genuinely want to, if you actually watch One Piece with no bias, no matter what age you are you'll love it. It may seem like a kiddy show but I've been watching it for years and haven't gotten sick of it at all. The easiest 10/10 I've ever given."
